         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <choice corresp="#a1">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>1, 64</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>93</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Everytime I saw you going through lands and villages, my mind and heart</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970a"/><citedRange>457</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Everytime I saw you going through lands and villages, my mind and heart leapt for joy, or everytime you entered the community the gods bowed their knees with añjali hands.  (cf 69, 213)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>379</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>69, 213</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">leapt for joy, or everytime you entered the community the gods bowed their knees</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2 #a3">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>71</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>47</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>12</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a2 #a3 #a4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Oder aber, [immer wenn] du in die Versammlung eintratest, neigten sich die Götter mit zusammengelegten Händen vor mir zu Erde [mit den Worten:] "Die Mutter des Buddha ist gekommen, Sie, die Leuchtende, [ist] auf der Stirn zu tragen."</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Or else, [whenever] you entered the assembly, the gods would bow to the ground before me with folded hands [saying:] "The mother of the Buddha has arrived, she, the radiant one, [must be] borne on the forehead."</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>303</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">with <hi>añjali</hi> hands.</seg></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a3 #a4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>88</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>150</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a4 #a5">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>208</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>203</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Jetzt ist mir die Hoffnung ganz zerstört worden, [denn] ich habe dich, die Sohnesperle, verloren, ich habe alle meine Glücksgüter [wtl. alle Glücksgüter des Selbstes] verloren.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Now my hope has been entirely destroyed, [for] I have lost you, pearl of sons, I have lost all my blessings [lit. all blessings of the self].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>127, 208</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#a5">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>85</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>127</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b2">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>203</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b3 #b4">
                  <seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>200</citedRange></bibl></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">Warum (nimmst(?)) du mir nicht (das Leben) fort? Streue meinen Körper auseinander!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Why do you not (take [my] life) from me? Scatter my body about!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>459</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
               <choice corresp="#b4">
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">... still I live nevertheless ...</seg></seg>
                  <seg><seg type="prim_transl">… still I live nevertheless … (575)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>368</citedRange></bibl></seg>
               </choice>
            </p>
